</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3356527FFA8FFE06D99F9E6FBBDF959" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B9036ACFFA8FFE06D99F9E6FBBDF959" blockId="18.[151,1436,152,1700]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="B95BEABEFFA8FFE06D99F9E6FEB0F980" bold="true" box="[198,298,1635,1661]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Biology.</emphasis>
The digestive tract of a dissected female [USNMENT00055937] was green, indicating that adults of this species rasp leaves or some other nonfloral part of its host plant.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
